jira-open [--print]

Open the JIRA ticket associated with the current git repo/branch in
the browser (https://storytel.atlassian.net/browse/<KEY>).

The JIRA key is resolved by trying these sources in order, first
match wins:

  1. The current branch name. If the first segment (before / or _)
     matches a JIRA key shape, e.g. DATA-1234/feat/foo -> DATA-1234,
     it is used.
  2. The title of the GitHub PR for the current branch (looked up
     via `gh pr view`), e.g. "DATA-1234: Implement defensive checks".
  3. Commit subjects on the current branch vs origin/<default>;
     subjects that START with a JIRA key are preferred.

With --print, the URL is printed instead of being opened. Otherwise
`open` (macOS) or `xdg-open` is used; if neither is available, the
URL is printed.

Requires: git. Optional: gh (for PR title lookup), open / xdg-open.
